tip.text: Good quality onigiri and just the right portion for lunch. Would come back again!
Amazing food and view! Jumbo size prawns, kona ribeye, and pear salad were all delicious. Great service and view as well. Highly recommend!
The lobster was to die for... I'd come back just for that. Also loved the foie gras and the desserts!
Loved the goma tofu and chef's homemade soba! The unagi was way over-grilled unfortunately.
Unfortunately did not enjoy most of the dishes :( I found the lamb ribs to be way too salty, raw scallop and greens were a mismatch. Best was the ricotta dumplings. Did not live up to the hype!
Sit at the chefs table for the full experience!
Great spot for Vietnamese food in Emeryville. Love the $10 noodle bowls!

formattedAddress: 320 Village Ln (at N Santa Cruz Ave)

tip.text: The Saba nigiri was literally the size of my palm!
Amazing pho! The bun cha ha noi was tasty as well, but not quite the authentic flavors from Hanoi.
Bun cha was delicious! The prices are high here but the quality and quantity are well worth it.
Cheesecake like texture and crust is not too sweet. Our favorite slice in town!

venue.name: Key West Key Lime Pie Company

tip.text: Lobster Benedict and key lime pie!! Pancake portions are huge, should've shared one instead of two ;)
Lobster was very fresh without excessive sauce. Conch fritters were a bit too salty for us though!
Overall good experience, but found the lunch pasta tasting too expensive at $38 pp. One of the dishes was a deep fried corn which was only average.
Favorite ice cream place in SF! Very very smooth and rich in flavor 😋
Good value for uni ikura don. Everything else is fairly priced.

formattedAddress: 111 N Atlantic Blvd Ste 241 (at W Garvey Ave.)

tip.text: Came here for a birthday dinner. We went for the $185 Ten menu. As a previously 2 star Michelin restaurant it was just ok - no surprising dishes and they did not pay attention to the smallest details.
Wait time isn't too bad on a weekday late night time. You can request for different noodle firmness with the ramen order. Fried rice is really delicious here too!

formattedAddress: 111 N Atlantic Blvd Ste 241 (at W Garvey Ave.)

tip.text: Try the duck pate, puff potato and eggs, duo beef dish, and peach dessert!
Love the fruit basket cake here, sweetness is just right. My whole family loved it!
Love their bacon wrapped mochi, and squid ink pasta if it's on the menu!
Lovely decor and friendly staff. Their scones are perfect and loved the savory treats! On Saturdays they only serve the full $32 menu vs different tiers on weekdays.
Birthday cake order here is perfect! They only do one type of cake with different flavor choices, cream is very fresh and cake base texture is great. Also love their green tea cookies at the counter!
Stick with what they're good at - dumplings. The beef soup noodle was flavorless.
Mango grapefruit dessert is yummy!
The free appetizer that came for every table at lunch was amazing. I was especially blown away by the tortellini al ragu!

formattedAddress: 181 Thompson St (btwn Bleecker & W Houston St)

tip.text: Lovely decor, our favorite dish was hands down the crab toast!

formattedAddress: 35 E 18th St (btwn Broadway & Park Ave S)

tip.text: My regular craving for the beef koja which has less fat than the short rib one. Portion is just right for lunch, get the umami fries if extra hungry.
Extra special nigiri or chirashi is my comfort food choice regularly.. consistent quality and type of fish every time.
Deluxe chirashi is worth the money!
Not a big salad fan but loved the guacamole green here (swapped for spinach). Was a little worried the jalapeño sauce would be spicy and the guy let me sample it first :)
Was able to make a last minute late lunch reservation here as we arrived in Nice, foie gras was the highlight of the meal!
Best French meal of my life to date. Flawless service and food presentation. Amazed a few times throughout the night...
Wait time could take be insane but perfect for an one person dinner, I've always ordered the chirashi which is awesome, but everything else look great too.
Squid ink pasta with uni is a must order here! Burrata was super fresh and worth the price. Recommended place!

venue.name: Obicà Mozzarella Bar Pizza e Cucina

tip.text: Came here for my birthday last year and it is still my favorite meal in the states to date! Nothing disappointed, lovely private area in the back dining room with tons of amazing beautiful dishes!

formattedAddress: 3799 Las Vegas Blvd S (at MGM Grand Hotel)

tip.text: Pea guacamole was our favorite dish. Everything else was a bit too greasy, also didn't think the food was worth the $ although the decor was nice.

formattedAddress: 38 E 19th St (btwn Park Ave S & Broadway)

tip.text: Excellent Kaiseki tasting experience! Especially loved the corn soup and the Hassun dishes. Matcha ice cream with white chocolate sauce was a perfect finish. Highly recommend!
Fast service on a crowded Sunday morning. Cute latte art inside a small to go cup!
